Currently the Embedded Crowd connectors allow you to alter the time between synchronizations to external sources, but you cannot specify a time or time frame for the jobs to run. For instance with large user bases in their external system, it would be better for performance to be able to schedule sync jobs outside of peak use hours.

With the current system, if you start your instance at 12am and set the sync interval for 24 hours, all it takes is a midday restart for that timeline to be thrown off.  It should be a job that can be scheduled from the UI, preferably in the Scheduled Jobs menu.

