The *Insert JIRA Issue* dialog box is a fantastic new feature in Confluence 3.5.

However, since you can insert a list of specific JIRA issues by specifying their individual issue keys in wiki markup:
{code}
{jira:<Issue Key 1>, <Issue Key 2>, <Issue Key 3>, etc.}
{code}

... wouldn't it be fantastic if any JIRA issues retrieved in the *Recently Viewed* and *Search* results of the *Insert JIRA Issue* dialog box, were multi-selectable? (Perhaps use check boxes for this.)

Then upon selecting multiple issues on the *Insert JIRA Issue* dialog box and inserting them onto the page, the issues would appear in the JIRA issues macro based on the wiki markup above.

----

If you do make this change, don't forget to change the name of this dialog box to *Insert JIRA Issues* (as you'll be able to insert more than 1 :-) ).

